main event: A saucer-shaped object was observed hovering about 200 ft above Lake Michigan, emitting a bright blinding light on July 5, 1965.
interesting points: The object was reported to be hovering and produced a bright light., The report concluded with 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION' due to lack of further evidence., A witness mentioned the object maneuvered in an erratic manner., The observer was fishing on the shore of Lake Michigan when they noticed the strange light., No photographs or physical evidence were provided in the documentation.
sighted object: saucer-shaped object emitting a bright light
witness description: fishermen observing the light for 15-20 minutes
